verses.text_plain: Let God arise, let his enemies be scattered: let them also that hate him flee before him.
verses.verse_html:
1Let God arise, let his enemies be scattered: let them also that hate him flee before him. ▼
▼ before…: Heb. from his face

footnotes.body_html: ▼ before…: Heb. from his face

verses.text_plain: As smoke is driven away, so drive them away: as wax melteth before the fire, so let the wicked perish at the presence of God.
verses.verse_html: 2As smoke is driven away, so drive them away: as wax melteth before the fire, so let the wicked perish at the presence of God.

verses.text_plain: But let the righteous be glad; let them rejoice before God: yea, let them exceedingly rejoice.
verses.verse_html:
3But let the righteous be glad; let them rejoice before God: yea, let them exceedingly rejoice. ▼
▼ exceedingly…: Heb. rejoice with gladness

footnotes.body_html: ▼ exceedingly…: Heb. rejoice with gladness

verses.text_plain: Sing unto God, sing praises to his name: extol him that rideth upon the heavens by his name Jah, and rejoice before him.
verses.verse_html: 4Sing unto God, sing praises to his name: extol him that rideth upon the heavens by his name Jah, and rejoice before him.

verses.text_plain: A father of the fatherless, and a judge of the widows, is God in his holy habitation.
verses.verse_html: 5A father of the fatherless, and a judge of the widows, is God in his holy habitation.

verses.text_plain: God setteth the solitary in families: he bringeth out those which are bound with chains: but the rebellious dwell in a dry land.
verses.verse_html:
6God setteth the solitary in families: he bringeth out those which are bound with chains: but the rebellious dwell in a dry land. ▼
▼ in families: Heb. in a house

footnotes.body_text: ▼ in families: Heb. in a house
footnotes.body_html: ▼ in families: Heb. in a house

verses.text_plain: O God, when thou wentest forth before thy people, when thou didst march through the wilderness; Selah:
verses.verse_html: 7O God, when thou wentest forth before thy people, when thou didst march through the wilderness; Selah:

verses.text_plain: The earth shook, the heavens also dropped at the presence of God: even Sinai itself was moved at the presence of God, the God of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 8The earth shook, the heavens also dropped at the presence of God: even Sinai itself was moved at the presence of God, the God of Israel.

verses.text_plain: Thou, O God, didst send a plentiful rain, whereby thou didst confirm thine inheritance, when it was weary.
verses.verse_html:
9Thou, O God, didst send a plentiful rain, whereby thou didst confirm thine inheritance, when it was weary. ▼
▼ send: Heb. shake out
 , ▼
▼ confirm: Heb. confirm it

footnotes.body_html: ▼ send: Heb. shake out
▼ confirm: Heb. confirm it

verses.text_plain: Thy congregation hath dwelt therein: thou, O God, hast prepared of thy goodness for the poor.
verses.verse_html: 10Thy congregation hath dwelt therein: thou, O God, hast prepared of thy goodness for the poor.

verses.text_plain: The Lord gave the word: great was the company of those that published it.
verses.verse_html:
11The Lord gave the word: great was the company of those that published it. ▼
▼ company: Heb. army

verses.text_plain: Kings of armies did flee apace: and she that tarried at home divided the spoil.
verses.verse_html:
12Kings of armies did flee apace: and she that tarried at home divided the spoil. ▼
▼ did…: Heb. did flee, did flee

footnotes.body_text: ▼ did…: Heb. did flee, did flee
footnotes.body_html: ▼ did…: Heb. did flee, did flee

verses.text_plain: Though ye have lien among the pots, yet shall ye be as the wings of a dove covered with silver, and her feathers with yellow gold.
verses.verse_html: 13Though ye have lien among the pots, yet shall ye be as the wings of a dove covered with silver, and her feathers with yellow gold.

verses.text_plain: When the Almighty scattered kings in it, it was white as snow in Salmon.
verses.verse_html:
14When the Almighty scattered kings in it, it was white as snow in Salmon. ▼
▼ in it…: or, for her, she

footnotes.body_text: ▼ in it…: or, for her, she
footnotes.body_html: ▼ in it…: or, for her, she

verses.text_plain: The hill of God is as the hill of Bashan; an high hill as the hill of Bashan.
verses.verse_html: 15The hill of God is as the hill of Bashan; an high hill as the hill of Bashan.

verses.text_plain: Why leap ye, ye high hills? this is the hill which God desireth to dwell in; yea, the Lord will dwell in it for ever.
verses.verse_html: 16Why leap ye, ye high hills? this is the hill which God desireth to dwell in; yea, the Lord will dwell in it for ever.

verses.text_plain: The chariots of God are twenty thousand, even thousands of angels: the Lord is among them, as in Sinai, in the holy place.
verses.verse_html:
17The chariots of God are twenty thousand, even thousands of angels: the Lord is among them, as in Sinai, in the holy place. ▼
▼ even…: or, even many thousands

footnotes.body_html: ▼ even…: or, even many thousands

verses.text_plain: Thou hast ascended on high, thou hast led captivity captive: thou hast received gifts for men; yea, for the rebellious also, that the Lord God might dwell among them.
verses.verse_html:
18Thou hast ascended on high, thou hast led captivity captive: thou hast received gifts for men; yea, for the rebellious also, that the Lord God might dwell among them. ▼
▼ for men: Heb. in the man

footnotes.body_text: ▼ for men: Heb. in the man
footnotes.body_html: ▼ for men: Heb. in the man

verses.text_plain: Blessed be the Lord, who daily loadeth us with benefits, even the God of our salvation. Selah.
verses.verse_html: 19Blessed be the Lord, who daily loadeth us with benefits, even the God of our salvation. Selah.

verses.text_plain: He that is our God is the God of salvation; and unto God the Lord belong the issues from death.
verses.verse_html: 20He that is our God is the God of salvation; and unto God the Lord belong the issues from death.

verses.text_plain: But God shall wound the head of his enemies, and the hairy scalp of such an one as goeth on still in his trespasses.
verses.verse_html: 21But God shall wound the head of his enemies, and the hairy scalp of such an one as goeth on still in his trespasses.

tokens.text: of such an one as goeth on still

verses.text_plain: The Lord said, I will bring again from Bashan, I will bring my people again from the depths of the sea:
verses.verse_html: 22The Lord said, I will bring again from Bashan, I will bring my people again from the depths of the sea:

verses.text_plain: That thy foot may be dipped in the blood of thine enemies, and the tongue of thy dogs in the same.
verses.verse_html:
23That thy foot may be dipped in the blood of thine enemies, and the tongue of thy dogs in the same. ▼
▼ dipped: or, red

verses.text_plain: They have seen thy goings, O God; even the goings of my God, my King, in the sanctuary.
verses.verse_html: 24They have seen thy goings, O God; even the goings of my God, my King, in the sanctuary.

verses.text_plain: The singers went before, the players on instruments followed after; among them were the damsels playing with timbrels.
verses.verse_html: 25The singers went before, the players on instruments followed after; among them were the damsels playing with timbrels.

verses.text_plain: Bless ye God in the congregations, even the Lord, from the fountain of Israel.
verses.verse_html:
26Bless ye God in the congregations, even the Lord, from the fountain of Israel. ▼
▼ from…: or, ye that are of the fountain of Israel

footnotes.body_text: ▼ from…: or, ye that are of the fountain of Israel
footnotes.body_html: ▼ from…: or, ye that are of the fountain of Israel

verses.text_plain: There is little Benjamin with their ruler, the princes of Judah and their council, the princes of Zebulun, and the princes of Naphtali.
verses.verse_html:
27There is little Benjamin with their ruler, the princes of Judah and their council, the princes of Zebulun, and the princes of Naphtali. ▼
▼ and their…: or, with their company

footnotes.body_text: ▼ and their…: or, with their company
footnotes.body_html: ▼ and their…: or, with their company

verses.text_plain: Thy God hath commanded thy strength: strengthen, O God, that which thou hast wrought for us.
verses.verse_html: 28Thy God hath commanded thy strength: strengthen, O God, that which thou hast wrought for us.

verses.text_plain: Because of thy temple at Jerusalem shall kings bring presents unto thee.
verses.verse_html: 29Because of thy temple at Jerusalem shall kings bring presents unto thee.

verses.text_plain: Rebuke the company of spearmen, the multitude of the bulls, with the calves of the people, till every one submit himself with pieces of silver: scatter thou the people that delight in war.
verses.verse_html:
30Rebuke the company of spearmen, the multitude of the bulls, with the calves of the people, till every one submit himself with pieces of silver: scatter thou the people that delight in war. ▼
▼ the company…: or, the beasts of the reeds
 , ▼
▼ scatter…: or, he scattereth

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the company…: or, the beasts of the reeds
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the company…: or, the beasts of the reeds
▼ scatter…: or, he scattereth

verses.text_plain: Princes shall come out of Egypt; Ethiopia shall soon stretch out her hands unto God.
verses.verse_html: 31Princes shall come out of Egypt; Ethiopia shall soon stretch out her hands unto God.

verses.text_plain: Sing unto God, ye kingdoms of the earth; O sing praises unto the Lord; Selah:
verses.verse_html: 32Sing unto God, ye kingdoms of the earth; O sing praises unto the Lord; Selah:

verses.text_plain: To him that rideth upon the heavens of heavens, which were of old; lo, he doth send out his voice, and that a mighty voice.
verses.verse_html:
33To him that rideth upon the heavens of heavens, which were of old; lo, he doth send out his voice, and that a mighty voice. ▼
▼ send…: Heb. give

verses.text_plain: Ascribe ye strength unto God: his excellency is over Israel, and his strength is in the clouds.
verses.verse_html:
34Ascribe ye strength unto God: his excellency is over Israel, and his strength is in the clouds. ▼
▼ clouds: or, heavens

verses.text_plain: O God, thou art terrible out of thy holy places: the God of Israel is he that giveth strength and power unto his people. Blessed be God.
verses.verse_html: 35O God, thou art terrible out of thy holy places: the God of Israel is he that giveth strength and power unto his people. Blessed be God.
